<section id="manifesto" class="section section--alt">
  <div class="container manifesto__inner">
    <div class="manifesto__content max-w-prose mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="manifesto__eyebrow">Our Manifesto</p>
      <h2 class="heading-lg">
        The internet was supposed to connect us. Instead, it took from us.
      </h2>
      <div class="manifesto__body">
        <p>
          Social platforms built empires on the labor of creators, moderators, and communities — then paid them nothing. They optimized for engagement, not understanding. For virality, not truth. For advertisers, not people. The result is a world more connected than ever and more divided than ever.
        </p>
        <p>
          Global Village exists to close that divide. Our news is reported by locals who live the story, fact-checked by real people, and placed into historical context — because understanding each other requires knowing where we've been. While legacy media puts knowledge behind paywalls and filters the world through foreign correspondents, we hand the microphone to the people who were there. And we will always be free.
        </p>
        <p>
          We close the language divide. Most platforms treat non-English speakers as an afterthought. Global Village supports 24 languages — with particular attention to underrepresented languages across West, East, Central, and Southern Africa — so communities can speak for themselves, in their own words, and be heard across borders.
        </p>
        <p>
          We close the economic divide. Moderators and translators are essential workers, not volunteers. The person who keeps a community safe at 2am deserves compensation, not a badge. The person who translates a post so it can reach a new audience deserves compensation, not a thank-you. Sixty percent of every dollar flows back to the people who built the community.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is not a social network. It is a village. And in this village, everyone eats.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

